# Finding 119
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Duplicate `resolveConfiguredRealtimeUrl` helper
- File + line(s): `packages/realtime/realtime-client-runtime/src/shared/runtime.js:79-89`, `apps/jskit-value-app/src/platform/realtime/realtimeRuntime.js:96-106`
- Why it can drift/fail: Runtime configuration resolution is duplicated between the package and the app runtime wrapper. Any change to env lookup rules must be duplicated.
- Concrete impact: App realtime URL resolution can diverge from package behavior.
- Exact remediation: Export `resolveConfiguredRealtimeUrl` from the realtime client runtime and reuse it in the app runtime.

WONT justification:
- This finding is scoped to client runtime/app wrapper code (`realtime-client-runtime` and `apps/.../src/platform/realtime`) and is being intentionally skipped while client templates are under active rewrite.

Signal to revisit later:
- Revisit once client-side rewrite is stabilized and client runtime duplication cleanup is back in scope.
